Preparation Course of Estonian gives the basic knowledge of the Estonian grammar and vocabulary and the initial knowledge of medical terms. Students will obtain knowledge and skills necessary to attend the main course Estonian for Students of Medicine.
The main topics (vocabulary & conversation): 
* Estonia and Estonians;
* Family
* States, nationalities, languages;
* Living quarters;
* Time (days, months, seasons. What time is it?)
* My day, my week;
* Food and drinks. Eating habits;
* In the shop. In the café;
* Christmas

The main topics (grammar):
*	Characteristic features of the Estonian language;
*	verb conjugation in the present and in the past simple;
*	question words;
*	Estonian cases (Singular: main cases, local cases, comitative case. Plural: nominative);
*	ma-infinitive and da-infinitive;
*	Numerals;
*	Comparison of adjectives;
*	(Personal) pronouns;
*	Imperative (singular form);
*	using prepositions and postpositions.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To teach the basics of Estonian grammar and basic vocabulary, start to introduce the special vocabulary of medicine, to practice medical terms in communicative situations and by writing texts, to prepare the students for the main language course Estonian for Students of Medicine. The intended outcome of the course by spring is pre-intermediate level skills in Estonian.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course the attendants will be able  * to understand and use Estonian cases, to conjugate Estonian verbs in the present and past tenses, to use the imperative, to compare adjectives, to use cardinal numbers and expressions of time. * to communicate in everyday situations in the street, in the shop, at a restaurant and to socialize in a group, to talk and write about her/himself, her/his family, home, work and eating habits, to express (dis)approval.
